     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>¶ I. C.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>FLe from the wrath that is to come</l>
      <l>You filthye adders broode,</l>
      <l>I cast that you perishe in your sinnes</l>
      <l>As giltie of your bloode.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>The wrath of God is kinde lid</l>
      <l>All suche to consume quite,</l>
      <l>That in the filthye soppes or dregges</l>
      <l>Of Egipt do delight</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Repent therfore I saye to you</l>
      <l>For mercye call betyme</l>
      <l>And learn to hate the stinkinge mud</l>
      <l>Uvhere wallow nune but swyne.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Here maye you reade the wofull ende</l>
      <l>Of suche as wont to vse</l>
      <l>Those wicked artes that God abhorres</l>
      <l>In tyme suche then refuse.</l>
   </lg>
   <trailer>¶ Finis.</trailer>
</div>
